%h2 The Four Phases

%p Manic depression is a <em>cyclic</em> disorder. It is most problematic as a seasonal disorder, because an episode that lasts for months may be fatal. But there are actually four overlapping cycles; the seasonal one is the longest, but the monthly (lunar), weekly, and daily cycles all follow the natural pattern of get energy, use energy, use strength, get strength, repeat.

