%p Bipolar disorder is either a #{Realm.M.name} disorder or an #{Realm.A.name} disorder, depending on who you ask, but I believe that it’s a disorder in all four realms. But the #{Realm.P.name} and #{Realm.F.name} realms are <em>measurable</em> and thus imbalances in those realms are more easily broken down into “eating too much and not exercising enough” or “spending too much and not earning enough”.

%p Nobody ever told me I was “talking too much and not listening enough” or “watching too much and not thinking enough”. Or at least, not in the sense that I should be able to <em>change</em> those behaviors, except by taking sedatives when I was manic and stimulants when depressed. Which is less than helpful when I was both at the same time or cycling rapidly between the two.

%p BipolarType offers advice in all four realms. Not only what you should do, but when you should do it: difficult but healthy behaviors need to be done <em>during their phase</em> to give you the largest chance for success. This is especially important for healthy behaviors that come <em>before</em> the unbalancing behaviors, as behaviors that come after tend to be a little more self-regulating.

